<abstract>
<t>In the especially initial stage of the transition from IPv4 to IPv6, it is hard to provide a complete set of IPv6 applications.  This memo proposes a mechanism of dual stack hosts using the technique called "Bump-in-the-Stack" in the IP security area. The mechanism allows the hosts to communicate with other IPv6 hosts using existing IPv4 applications.</t></abstract></front>

